{
  "buggy_files": [
    "sound/pci/hda/hda_intel.c"
  ],
  "buggy_functions": [
    "azx_init_chip"
  ],
  "confidence": 0.85,
  "reasoning": "The bug is in the azx_init_chip function (line 1209). After suspend/resume, the CORB/RIRB (Command/Response Ring Buffers) hardware is not properly reinitialized. The function has an early return check at line 1211-1212 that prevents reinit when chip->initialized is already set. During resume (line 2561 in azx_resume), azx_init_chip is called with full_reset=1, but if chip->initialized remains 1 (or if chip->single_cmd is 1 from a previous timeout), the critical CORB/RIRB initialization at line 1222-1223 (azx_init_cmd_io call) is skipped. This causes the codec to be unable to communicate properly after resume, leading to the timeout errors: 'azx_get_response timeout, switching to polling mode', 'No response from codec, disabling MSI', and 'azx_get_response timeout, switching to single_cmd mode'. The fix requires ensuring CORB/RIRB is always reinitialized during resume by either: (1) resetting chip->initialized=0 before or at the start of azx_init_chip when full_reset=1, (2) resetting chip->single_cmd=0 during resume, or (3) modifying the early return to check the full_reset parameter."
}

code_changes.new_string:
{
  "buggy_files": [
    "sound/pci/hda/hda_intel.c"
  ],
  "buggy_functions": [
    "azx_init_chip",
    "azx_resume"
  ],
  "confidence": 0.90,
  "reasoning": "The bug manifests when codec communication times out during resume, triggering single_cmd mode (line 951 sets chip->single_cmd=1). The root cause is in azx_init_chip (line 1209-1230): at line 1222-1223, CORB/RIRB initialization via azx_init_cmd_io is skipped if chip->single_cmd==1. Once single_cmd mode is activated by a timeout, it is never reset, so on subsequent suspend/resume cycles, azx_init_chip skips CORB/RIRB reinitialization even though it's called with full_reset=1. During resume (line 2539-2566), azx_resume does not reset chip->single_cmd to 0 before calling azx_init_chip, so the CORB/RIRB remains uninitialized. When snd_hda_resume at line 2563 tries to communicate with the codec, it times out because the ring buffers are not properly initialized. The fix requires either: (1) resetting chip->single_cmd=0 in azx_resume before calling azx_init_chip, (2) forcing CORB/RIRB reinitialization in azx_init_chip when full_reset=1 regardless of single_cmd state, or (3) unconditionally calling azx_init_cmd_io during full_reset."
}

