    "sound/pci/hda/hda_intel.c"
  ],
  "buggy_functions": [
    "azx_init_chip",
    "azx_resume"
  ],
  "confidence": 0.90,
  "reasoning": "The bug manifests when codec communication times out during resume, triggering single_cmd mode (line 951 sets chip->single_cmd=1). The root cause is in azx_init_chip (line 1209-1230): at line 1222-1223, CORB/RIRB initialization via azx_init_cmd_io is skipped if chip->single_cmd==1. Once single_cmd mode is activated by a timeout, it is never reset, so on subsequent suspend/resume cycles, azx_init_chip skips CORB/RIRB reinitialization even though it's called with full_reset=1. During resume (line 2539-2566), azx_resume does not reset chip->single_cmd to 0 before calling azx_init_chip, so the CORB/RIRB remains uninitialized. When snd_hda_resume at line 2563 tries to communicate with the codec, it times out because the ring buffers are not properly initialized. The fix requires either: (1) resetting chip->single_cmd=0 in azx_resume before calling azx_init_chip, (2) forcing CORB/RIRB reinitialization in azx_init_chip when full_reset=1 regardless of single_cmd state, or (3) unconditionally calling azx_init_cmd_io during full_reset."
}

